div.div: Created new tag v0.12.0 in jim60105/docker-infinite-image-browsing
Commented on #2382 Some incorrect usage related to the recent `shell=False` issue

I have merged the change to the dev branch. I hope this will run fine on all platforms... including runpod, vastai and others like colab. I can confirm the LoRA trainning can start on WSL2 docker.
Note that I added the --do_not_use_shell because I am unsure if it will be adopted or what the current default value is.

build: Update Dockerfile stages name and upgrade ffmpeg
- Renamed the build stage comments in Dockerfile from "Build stage for requirements" and "Preparing final stage" to simply "Build stage" and "Final stage" respectively. - Updated the ffmpeg version in Dockerfile from 6.1.1 to 7.0-1. - Similar comment changes made in nuitka.Dockerfile where "Preparing final stage" was revised to "Final stage". - In nuitka.Dockerfile, removal of specific shell commands has been uncommented to prevent the container from executing arbitrary commands.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

refactor: move Nuitka to a new dockerfile
- Added a new prettier configuration file specifying 2 spaces for tab width and disallowing the use of tabs. - Changed the Dockerfile's build stage to include the installation of `libxcb1` instead of `dumb-init`. - Un-commented the cleanup section of Dockerfile, removing python cached files for a tidier build. - Modified how licenses are copied with new ownership permissions. - Reorganized Dockerfile's final stage to include new environment and configuration setups. - Removed various insecure commands from the Dockerfile's final stage. - Dockerfile's final stage now properly handles SIGINT signals and uses `dumb-init` as PID 1. - Removed the build stages for Nuitka compiler since they seem to be unnecessary. - Added a comment in `docker-compose.yml` indicating the option of specifying a different Dockerfile for the build. - Created a new Nuitka.Dockerfile for compiling Python code into standalone executables. This file includes many of the same changes as outlined for Dockerfile above.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>
